        <body>       

                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Aylmer. Ontario&#44; Canada<lb/>
                Sept. 18<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1888.<lb/></p>
            <p>To Rabbi Morra&#239;s<lb/>
                Dear Sir&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>Having heard of the favor<lb/> you hold toward all people outside your church&#44;<lb/> and the good&#45;will with which you are<lb/> held&#44; I take the liberty to propound a few<lb/> questions to you who are so well versed<lb/> in the usages and rites of the orthodox<lb/> Jewish Church&#44; and in which I take a<lb/> special interest.<lb/></p>
            <p>&#40;1&#41; Is not the Mikva&#44; or plunge bath an<lb/> essential rite to an orthodox Jew&#44; and<lb/> can sprinkling be substituted for it in<lb/> any case or under any circumstance&#63;<lb/></p>
            <p>&#40;2&#41; Can you substitute the Mikva for<lb/> circumcision&#63;<lb/></p>
            <p>&#40;3&#41; Is not the circumcision which is performed on<lb/> the 8<hi rend="sup">th</hi> day&#44; really intended to alleviate<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>2<lb/></p>
            <p>suffering&#44; the circumcision being a<lb/> physical operation&#63;<lb/></p>
            <p>&#40;4&#41; Is not circumcision one of the<lb/> covenants showing the interest of God<lb/> for the welfare of His people&#44; morally&#44;<lb/> physically &#38; spiritually&#63;<lb/></p>
            <p>&#40;5&#41; Is the Mikva&#44; the baptism&#44; and<lb/> is it not the source of christian baptism&#63;<lb/></p>
            <p>I beg you to answer these<lb/> questions&#44; as it is of very great im&#45;<lb/>portance to me&#44; especially as the answers<lb/> come from a person of authority.<lb/></p>
            <p>Your Obedient Servant<lb/>
                A. S. Sowerby<lb/>
                Pastor Bap. Church<lb/>
                Aylmer<lb/> Ontario<lb/> Canada.<lb/></p>
                
            <p>P. S. &#40;6&#41; Under what circumstances do you <hi rend="underline">sprinkle</hi> an individual&#63;<lb/>  &#40;7&#41; At what age is the Mikva administered&#63; &#40;I mean the earliest age&#41;.<lb/></p>
            </body>
